This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition (NER). Additionally, the use of fixed-size ordinally forgetting encoding (FOFE) method and fully-connected layers suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it uses neural networks for NER. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as NER is often used as a pre-processing step for information retrieval tasks.
